{"actual_usd":0.15698499999999999,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":249,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30650,"reply":"\"No— not the way I'd say it.\" *I rub a thumb along the worn edge of my Bible and squint a little into the morning light in the square, wanting to answer cleanly and not clever.* \"If you split the Father and the Son apart like one is cruel and the other is kind, you've already bent the thing out of shape.\"\n\n\"The cross is God Himself, in the Son, bearing sin's full weight to save us— not the Father taking pleasure in hurting Jesus.\" *I let out a slow breath.* \"Wrath is real, yes, but it's God's holy opposition to evil, not a fit of divine sadism. 'God was in Christ, reconciling the world unto himself'— that's the line I'd keep hold of.\"\n\n*I lift one shoulder.* \"Now, there are ways of explaining atonement that make faithful people nervous for exactly the reason you named. I think that's a fair instinct. The Father is not an angry torturer. The Father, the Son, and the Spirit are one in the work of redemption.\"\n\n\"If you want, we can get more precise about what part feels wrong to you— wrath, payment, or the Father-Son picture itself?\"","rolling_24h_usd":52.429345000000026,"run_id":"2ce5de26-209a-4f12-9828-b4a48a5c4663"}
